        "heading": "From Open Sea to the World Stage",
        "paragraph_1": "In 1979, the story of Nancy Vuu did not begin in a studio; it began on the open sea. I was a one-year-old baby, carried into the unknown by parents who possessed the rarest kind of wealth: the courage to dream. Leaving the shores of Vietnam as refugees, they sacrificed their lineage to secure my freedom. They traded the only world they knew for a promise they couldn't see—so that decades later, I could return with a vision that spans continents.",
        "paragraph_2": "But the journey wasn't linear. Before the silks and the runways, I spent years navigating the high-stakes world of corporate leadership as a Vice President. I had planned a quiet transition to motherhood when a radical spiritual encounter shifted my entire trajectory. It was a \"Divine Yes\" that pulled me into fashion—not to follow trends, but to facilitate the restoration of true and sovereign identity.",
        "pullquote": "\"This is the foundation of our house: A legacy of survival turned into a mission of restoration.\""
